Verity: The Future of Elections
Exceptionally easy to use. Versatile for lasting value. Loaded with features that inspire voter trust. Verity is unlike any voting system you’ve ever seen. 

  






Prepare


Define


Vote


Count & Report


Audit



Easy. Versatile. Trustworthy



Easy – Designed with humans in mind, Verity is intuitive and easy for voters and election officials to use.

Versatile – Verity’s uniquely flexible hardware and software approach means the system adapts as your needs change.

Trustworthy – Comprehensive audit logs and reports shed light on user activity and build stakeholder confidence.

	All Verity components are based on a single integrated platform, providing user-friendly end-to-end election management for all voting types.

At the polling place. Voters scan their paper ballots on the Verity Scan digital scanning device.  Voters with disabilities mark their ballots on the accessible Verity Touch Writer ballot marking device; then scan them, along with other voters’ ballots, using Verity Scan. For electronic voting, voters use the Verity Touch DRE device.

Absentee and by-mail ballots. Verity Central is a scalable, high-speed scanning solution that uses Hart-integrated COTS scanners at affordable price points. Verity Central eliminates the need for pre-sorting ballots as it scans and records cast vote records. And Verity Central's second-generation onscreen adjudication features make it easy for election officials to quickly and accurately resolve questionable ballot marks.

Election management. The Verity Data and Verity Build software applications enable election officials to import and manage election data, design ballots and define and deploy elections, all within a single, unified, user-friendly workflow - no coding skills required. The Verity Count tabulation and reporting software provides standard and customized reports on a wide variety of cast vote record and audit information gathered from other voting system components. Verity Count's user-friendly dashboards enable election officials to monitor progress on Election Night, or to perform post-election audits, in a highly filterable way.








